HEADWORD: Highland
<hw>High"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Elevated or
mountainous land; (often in the <pluf>pl.</pluf>) an elevated region or
country; <as>as, the <ex>Highlands</ex> of Scotland</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Highland fling</b></col>, <cd>a dance peculiar to the
Scottish Highlanders; a sort of hornpipe.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>highland</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: highland
<hw>highland</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>of, located in, or characteristic
of high or hilly country. Contrasted to <contr>lowland</contr>.</def>
<mark>[prenominal]</mark> [Narrower terms: <stype>alpestrine, subalpine
</stype>; <stype>alpine</stype>; <stype>mountain(prenominal) </stype>;
<stype>mountainous </stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> upland.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

